Car Makes & Models









Q:
What are the different types of transportation?


A:
According to "The Geography of the Transport System," different types of transportation include cars, buses, trains, planes, boats and bicycles. The type of transportation chosen generally depends on the costs associated with travel and the length of the trip.


See Full Answer

Filed Under:


Car Makes & Models












Q:
What is a non-commercial vehicle?


A:
A non-commercial vehicle is a vehicle that is used strictly for transportation purposes. An example of a non-commercial vehicle is a family car, van or SUV. A non-commercial vehicle is a private vehicle that is not intended for use for earning income.


See Full Answer

Filed Under:


Car Makes & Models












Q:
What is the factory-recommended tire size for a 1999 Ford Ranger?


A:
The factory-recommended tire size for the 1999 Ford Ranger depends on the style of Ranger, according to Firestone. The Ranger XL with regular cab and two-wheel drive originally came with P205/75R14 tires. An XLT with the same configuration had P225/70R15 tires.


